- Only use Pathname when really necessary.
- Designate and support a location for files containing user-defined page types.
- Move the template directory out of the site root.
- Add Blog page types.
  * Blog::Index (/diary/)
    .posts
  * Blog::Archive (/diary/2010/, /diary/2010/09/, /diary/2010/09/15/)
  * Blog::Post (/diary/2010/09/15/picnic-in-the-woods/)
    .date
    @title
    @summary
    @content
  * Blog::Comment (/diary/2010/09/15/picnic-in-the-woods/comment-1)
  * Blog::RSSIndex (/diary/rss-feed/)
  * Blog::AtomIndex (/diary/atom-feed/)
  * figure out how to store category information (/diary/categories/cheese/, /diary/categories/pasta/, /diary/categories/fruit/)
- (Maybe) Support updating page attributes via POST request.
- Implement some sort of page caching.
- (Maybe) Integrate a Web-based file manager and editor (such as http://elrte.org/) to make a sort of CMS.
